title: Understanding Descending Order
text: When sorting in descending order, the values are arranged from the highest to the lowest. In the context of alphabetical sorting, this means starting from the letter closest to 'Z' and moving towards 'A'.

title: Alphabetical Order
text: In alphabetical order, 'Sycamore' comes after 'Hickory' and 'Elm' because 'S' is later in the alphabet than 'H' and 'E'.

title: Identify the First Letter
text: Identify the first letter of each street name: Hickory, Elm, and Sycamore. Which letter is closest to 'Z'?

title: Determine the Order
text: Based on the first letters, which street name should appear first when sorted in descending order?
